	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well .. here's more insite of the wolf. He was spawned 5 known times yesterday. We here in a group of 4 and we wanted to get this item for each of our memembers.<br><br>The first time, it was just a friend and I. I watched the said spawn point, and he trained the wolves. Nothing. Then all of the sudden there is an ooc that he was just killed ( ugh ). He never spawned east of the spire before the hill. <br><br>Now, we  get a couple more friends, one a druid, and we decided to hunt the giants while we killed the local wolves. He spawned twice in a 20 minute period right there next to us ( there are about 3 wolf spawn points infront of the giant fort ).<br><br>A friend leaves, and we continue hunting but we lax on killing the wolves, nothing. We all log and come back in later on that night. We hunt the giant fort again and start in full swing for the wolves. We got him to spawn two more times. First one, no clue where, we had druid track and pull him while we took care of a named giant we pulled at the time of spawn.<br>Second time, wolf spawned south west ( yes west ) of the spires.<br><br>So .. This spawn is truely random. We got him to spawn 4 times while killing giants and local wolves. Though, I bet you can get him to spawn just by killing the wolves. A druid, ranger, or maybe even a bard ( they have track too ) is necessary to find the blood wolf. He'll spawn and roam just like any other wolf in the zone.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
